Yvonne Mbekwa, 27, has been missing since June 5, along with her two -year-old daughter. Her family said she had been travelling to P o rt St Johns but got worried when she failed to make contact with any of her relatives or friends . With the recent horrifying attacks on women and children making headlines all over the country Yvonne s family is now fearing that both mother and daughter may have been killed . Port St John s police spokeswoman Captain Nozuko Handile said Yvonne was reported missing last week and that so far there have been no leads. She has urged anyone with information to come forward . Contact PSJ police on 047-564 &#8211; 1189/1621 or Crime Stop 08600-10111 or to SMS CrimeLine 32211